oxy_webhelp_navlinks = {"sec_keys_c-d4802e7487":{"topics":[{"title":"Encrypting and digitally signing email messages","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can set HCL Notes® to digitally sign and encrypt email messages you send to other Notes users or to users over the Internet. <\/p>","href":"sec_keys_mail_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_keys_mail_t"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_keys_mail_t-d4802e7510","topics":[]},{"title":"Mail security","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can access your mail security options through the User Security window.<\/p>","href":"sec_mail_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_mail_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_mail_c-d4802e7529","topics":[]},{"title":"Mail encryption failure","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">The \"Mail Encryption Failure\" dialog box appears when you want to encrypt an outgoing mail message and HCL Notes® can't find the recipient's certificate to encrypt the message. <\/p>","href":"sec_mail_encrypfail_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_mail_encrypfail_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_mail_encrypfail_c-d4802e7540","topics":[]},{"title":"Location configuration for signing Internet-style (S\/MIME) mail ","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can view your Internet mail address information.<\/p>","href":"sec_mail_smime_sign_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_mail_smime_sign_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_mail_smime_sign_c-d4802e7556","topics":[]},{"title":"Edit locations (format for sending mail to Internet addresses)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">HCL Notes® Internet-style mail uses secure MIME (S\/MIME) protocols for sending and receiving encrypted and signed mail. Internet-style Notes mail is required to secure mail to people over the Internet, and is optional to secure your mail to other Notes users.<\/p>","href":"sec_editloc_inetmail_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"N10001"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"N10001-d4802e7569","topics":[]},{"title":"Edit locations (Internet Mail Address)","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">HCL Notes® Internet-style mail uses secure MIME (S\/MIME) protocols for sending and receiving encrypted and signed mail. Internet-style Notes mail (S\/MIME) is required to secure your mail to people over the Internet, and is optional to secure your mail to other Notes users.<\/p>","href":"sec_editloc_inetmailadd_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_editloc_inetmailadd_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_editloc_inetmailadd_c-d4802e7591","topics":[]},{"title":"Incoming mail","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can select the type of format in which you prefer to receive your incoming mail.<\/p>","href":"sec_mail_incoming_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_mail_incoming_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_mail_incoming_c-d4802e7613","topics":[]},{"title":"Encryption certificate configuration for Internet-style (S\/MIME) mail","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can view details about your encryption certificate, used for mail with people outside of HCL Notes® and for mail from Notes users if you are configured to receive Internet-style (S\/MIME) mail.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_encryp_smime_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"N10001"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"N10001-d4802e7626","topics":[]},{"title":"Certificate configuration for Internet-style (S\/MIME) mail","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can view the Internet certificates located in your User ID. The certificates listed are the certificates that you can use to send and receive secure and signed mail through HCL Notes® with others over the Internet. One of these Internet certificates must be designated as the default signing certificate. <\/p>","href":"sec_cert_smime_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_smime_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_smime_c-d4802e7646","topics":[]},{"title":"Using dual Internet certificates for encryption and signatures","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You use your Internet certificate to sign messages that you send. Other people use your Internet certificate to encrypt messages they are sending to you. This is similar to how HCL Notes® certificates work. However, if you have more than one Internet certificate, you may be able to use one Internet certificate for signing messages and another Internet certificate for people to use to encrypt mail messages. <\/p>","href":"sec_cert_dualinternet_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_dualinternet_t"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_dualinternet_t-d4802e7663","topics":[]},{"title":"Select default signing certificate","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You if you have more than one Internet certificate, you can select which one to act as the default signing certificate.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_signing_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_signing_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_signing_c-d4802e7681","topics":[]},{"title":"Internet-style Notes mail options","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can configure your Internet certificates for sending and receiving secure mail with people outside of HCL Notes®. <\/p>","href":"sec_mail_inetoptions_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_mail_inetoptions_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_mail_inetoptions_c-d4802e7694","topics":[]},{"title":"Creating new public keys","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If you lost your User ID, or someone has taken it to access your data, you should change your password and create new public keys (a new Notes® multi-purpose certificate and a new Notes international encryption certificate). <\/p>","href":"sec_keys_new_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_keys_new_t"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_keys_new_t-d4802e7710","topics":[]},{"title":"Publishing your Notes certificate for others to access","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You may want to publish your certificate containing your public key so others can use it to encrypt data being sent to you. The certificate can be published in the HCL Domino® Directory or sent to an individual, so that person can publish it in their Contacts. How to publish your public key depends on whether or not you are an HCL Notes® mail user.<\/p>","href":"sec_pub_cert_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_keys_mail_t"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_keys_mail_t-d4802e7729","topics":[]},{"title":"Certificates in your ID file","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can display all HCL Notes® and Internet certificates that are found in your User ID.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_idfile_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_idfile_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_idfile_c-d4802e7748","topics":[]},{"title":"Merge certificate into your User ID","href":"sec_id_mergcert_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_id_mergcert_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_id_mergcert_c-d4802e7764","topics":[]},{"title":"Examining certificates","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can examine your certificates from your Contacts. <\/p>","href":"sec_cert_examine_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_examine_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_examine_c-d4802e7774","topics":[]},{"title":"Certificate authorities and the certificates they issue","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can view all of the Notes® and Internet certificate authority (CA) certificates that you trust.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_authorities_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"N10001"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"N10001-d4802e7788","topics":[]},{"title":"Requesting certificates or cross certificates","href":"sec_cert_requestcert_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_requestcert_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_requestcert_c-d4802e7804","topics":[]},{"title":"Creating a cross certificate on demand","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">In the following situations you may be prompted to create a cross certificate.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_ondemand_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_ondemand_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_ondemand_c-d4802e7814","topics":[]},{"title":"Requesting cross certificates or merging information","href":"sec_cert_requestcross_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_requestcross_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_requestcross_c-d4802e7827","topics":[]},{"title":"Retrieving certificates and cross certificates from your home server","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">To access HCL Notes® servers in other domains, to verify digital signatures, or to encrypt messages using S\/MIME, you must have cross certificates in your Contacts. You can add to your Contacts Internet certificates and Notes and Internet cross certificates from the HCL Domino® Directory on your home\/mail server.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_homeserver_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"N10001"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"N10001-d4802e7838","topics":[]},{"title":"Advanced certificate details","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can view details about your selected HCL Notes® or Internet certificate.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_advdetails_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_advdetails_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_advdetails_c-d4802e7860","topics":[]},{"title":"Trust details","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">When you are viewing certificates from people and services you can view Trust Details for a selected certificate. Trust Details displays the name of the certificate, and what kind of trust you have established for it. The following are reasons why you might trust a certificate.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_trustdetails_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_trustdetails_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_trustdetails_c-d4802e7876","topics":[]},{"title":"Certificates for people or services","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can view all of the HCL Notes® and Internet certificates that you trust and don't trust for specific people or services.<\/p>","href":"sec_cert_peopleserv_c.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_cert_peopleserv_c"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_cert_peopleserv_c-d4802e7887","topics":[]},{"title":"To delete your Notes pending public keys","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">If you have HCL Notes® pending keys that you do not need anymore, you can delete the keys from your User ID. You get Notes pending keys when you request new Notes public keys. The reason you might not need your Notes pending keys any longer is if you've decided to not update your Notes certificates with new public keys. In this case, pending keys have not yet been used for any purpose, therefore it is safe to delete them, assuming you definitely don't want to complete your request for new public keys.<\/p>","href":"sec_keys_delpend_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_keys_delpend_t"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_keys_delpend_t-d4802e7903","topics":[]},{"title":"Exporting a safe copy of your User ID","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">When renewing HCL Notes® certificates or requesting new public keys using removable media or another mail program, you need to create a safe copy of your User ID and save it to removable media or directory that you can access.<\/p>","href":"sec_id_safecopy_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_id_safecopy_t"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_id_safecopy_t-d4802e7931","topics":[]},{"title":"To import new information from removable media into your User ID","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">When you import new information into your User ID, such as a new public key, you may need to make sure to update any copies of your User ID as well.<\/p>","href":"sec_id_removemedia_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_id_removemedia_t"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_id_removemedia_t-d4802e7948","topics":[]},{"title":"Key rollover","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Key rollover is the process used to update the set of Notes® public and private keys that is stored in your  ID file. This set of keys may need to be replaced - for instance, to increase security by updating to larger keys, or to recover if your private key has been compromised in some way.<\/p>","href":"sec_keys_rollover_t.html","attributes":{"data-id":"sec_keys_rollover_t"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"sec_keys_rollover_t-d4802e7962","topics":[]}]}};